div.h1: WAL Mode: Concurrent Readers and Writer

div.p: Writer appends frames to WAL file sequentially. Never blocks on readers!
Database file unchanged during transaction. Only updated at checkpoint.
Each reader captures max_frame at transaction start:

ul.li: Reader A (max=0): Sees only database, ignores all WAL frames
Reader B (max=2): Sees frames 1-2 (committed at frame 3)
Reader C (max=3): Sees frames 1-3, but frame 4 is uncommitted No blocking! Writers append while readers query.
